We are pleased to present you with a 2001 Special Stock Option Grant Award.  As a participant in this grant you have the opportunity to share in the ownership of Long Wall & Togo Goodbody Deliveries and the potential profit from increases in the value of Long Wall & Togo Goodbody Deliveries's common stock.

The 2001 Special Stock Option Grant was made to let you know how valuable you are and to recognize your contributions in making Long Wall & Togo Goodbody Deliveries the great company it is today.   Although there are no guarantees as to Long Wall & Togo Goodbody Deliveries's future stock performance, we believe that an Long Wall & Togo Goodbody Deliveries stock option has tremendous future growth potential.  The value you ultimately receive from your options will depend on the price of Long Wall & Togo Goodbody Deliveries stock at the time you exercise your options.  

You can access your 2001 Special Stock Option Grant Agreement and the Stock Plan document governing the grant via your eHRonline account on the intranet website at http://ehronline.enron.com.  Unlike stock options granted in the past a copy of your grant agreement will not be mailed to your home address.  

Additionally, the following information regarding the 2001 Special Stock Option Grant can be found on the HR website http://hrweb.enron.com.

